I’ve been getting apprenticeship questions a lot more recently, so a friend suggested I make an official post about them!

I, personally, have no interest in taking an apprentice at this point in my life. 

If you are looking for an apprenticeship, here’s some advice! 

❤️Build your art portfolio with ONLY complete pieces! No sketches or anything unfinished. I would also advise not having anything that is on lined or scratch paper. 

❤️Find a tattooer who’s work looks most similar to the type of tattooing you want to do. You want to do traditional? Find a traditional artist. Realism? Realism artist.

❤️Get tattooed by them. A lot. A lot of us aren’t going to give an apprenticeship to a complete stranger. Ask this person for apprenticeship advice directly. Even if they dont want to be your mentor, maybe they can point you in the right direction.

❤️Consider how much time you can dedicate to your apprenticeship and if it is realistic. Most apprenticeships are not paid. Are you in a position to essentially be going to school?

❤️Draw. Draw everyday. Even when you dont want to. 

❤️If you are turned down for apprenticeships, i heavily suggest not buying equipment and teaching yourself. 

Be realistic with your goals when it comes to being a tattooer. And be respectful 🌈

🧡💛EXCITING NEWS💚💙💜
About to begin the next chapter of my life with two of the best friends anyone could hope to have in their lifetime!
@stabqueen @durbin_designs , and I are opening our own studio- 🖤Wisteria Piercing & Tattoo💜
4202 Hamilton Ave- in the heart of Northside!

A lot of blood, sweat, and tears have gone into this project of ours, and we’re so happy to get to share it with everyone!

If you have an appointment with me AFTER October 3rd, it will be here! 

That being said, this is my final week at Cincinnati Tattoo & Piercing. A bittersweet moment as it has been my home for more than half of my career. I’ve got a lot of memories made here and I’m sad to let it go.

✨ANNOUNCEMENT, PLEASE SHARE✨

So pleased to introduce you to our new studio, 
💐Wisteria Piercing and Tattoo💐 
Located at 4202 Hamilton avenue in Northside. As of next week, I will be working only at this location. I can’t believe I’m saying this but I am officially a business owner! Not only that, but I own a shop with two people I love and respect more than anything. Brandon and Alexis, thank you so much for doing this with me and trusting me. Only we know the depths of how hard this truly has been. Working for Cincinnati Tattoo for the last 10 years has been so special to me, it is extremely bittersweet. Thank you so much to my family and friends for supporting me through this journey, thank you to my Boss for believing in me, and thank you to every single one of you who came to get a piercing done. I love you all so much, and I’m looking forward to what the future holds for us 💙
